Personally, I'd use "divider" to specify things that maintained an almost-50% duty cycle, and "timer" as a more generic term, especially for a signal that's asserted one cycle per N. But it's not like wikipedia's article on the 8254 agrees with my inclination.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Wed Dec 29, 2010 11:46 pm</p><hr />
